Hop to adventure with Peter Rabbit and his two closest pals, Benjamin and Lily,
in these exciting tales that feature a modern take on Beatrix Potter's beloved
characters... and some new ones as well! Children learn valuable skills and the
meaning of friendship when they join Peter and his friends as they try to find
a great - and safe! - place to eat the radishes they took from Mr. McGregor's
garden. Plus, Peter must rescue Jemima Puddle-Duck from the evil Mr. Tod,
Squirrel Nutkin helps the trio build a hideout, Benjamin leads the way on a
strawberry raid, Peter, Benjamin and Lily accidentally bring home Mr. McGregor's
sleeping cat, Peter searches for Jemima's missing egg, a four-leaf clover might
not be as lucky as Lily had hoped, the search for a mother's day gift turns into
a wild adventure, and hours more excitement! So cuddle up next to your little
bunny and take off together to some places you know and love, and new ones you're
about to discover.

Produced by Brown Bag Films and Silvergate Media.


When Peter loses Cotton-tail's beloved squeaky rabbit toy, he must get it back!

When Peter learns that his father once crash-landed a flying machine
into Mr. McGregor's garden, he vows to find it and fly it home!
